Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.81,0:00:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful yet fleeting, it flickers and perishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.15,0:00:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Words cannot describe what lay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.90,0:00:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that remains is sadness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.01,0:00:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and long-neglected memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.21,0:01:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It may seem strange to you that we\Nexpend so much effort on incense,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,almost to the point of obsession.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.01,0:02:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Smells are extremely potent things, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.59,0:02:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When hearing a sweet fragrance, you\Noften find that long-forgotten vistas,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.64,0:02:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,beams of light, or even poems come to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.31,0:02:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I think I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you’ve no doubt gathered, Toudaiji is merely a pseudonym.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.78,0:02:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its real name is the Rannatai.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.16,0:02:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The radicals which compose these\Ncharacters can be read tou-dai-ji, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.16,0:02:29.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.54,0:02:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Rannatai is no ordinary wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.67,0:02:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is said that its owner will become a great conqueror.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.59,0:02:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Ashikaga Yoshimasa and Oda\NNobunaga have partaken of the Rannatai
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.13,0:02:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the Toudaiji Temple’s Great Treasure Room.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.39,0:02:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.80,0:02:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if the Rannatai is stored in the\NGreat Treasure Room, what is it doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.60,0:02:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are actually two Rannatai.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.77,0:03:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Word reached us that Lady Ruri owned the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should be obvious why we seek the Toudaiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.33,0:03:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us begin before dawn breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.80,0:03:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will play Taketori-no-Kou this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.26,0:03:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is that played?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, two reference scents are heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.39,0:03:30.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One is designated as Princess\NKaguya, the other as the Old Woodcutter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.06,0:03:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, five scents, including the\NPrincess and Old Man, are heard in turn.{fade}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.32,0:03:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each player must determine whether the scent\Nis the Princess, the Old Man, or something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A player with a correct answer moves on to the\Nnext round, while one with an incorrect answer…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.29,0:03:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Loses then and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.59,0:04:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakarai-dono, did you not say something about a Nue earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.05,0:04:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you mean the mythical beast with a\Nmonkey’s head, tiger’s limbs and so forth?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.18,0:04:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a snake’s tail. Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.31,0:04:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s merely a picture assembled from stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.32,0:04:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who see its monkey portion say they saw a monkey,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.57,0:04:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and those who see its tiger portion say they saw a tiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.37,0:04:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, the story never explicitly describes the creature,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.29,0:04:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but rather implies that its form\Ndiffers depending on where it is seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.18,0:04:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this Nue your Mononoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.14,0:04:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.43,0:04:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have not discerned its Form as of yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.44,0:04:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder when it will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.69,0:05:00.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, perhaps it already has.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.91,0:05:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.88,0:05:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reference scent, Princess Kaguya, is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.18,0:05:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this scent?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.98,0:05:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell it is some sort of agar, but its depth is unfathomable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.57,0:05:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s no ordinary medicine seller.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.94,0:05:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s as though the skin of my scalp is shuddering.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.61,0:05:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Old Man is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.12,0:05:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the same as the Kaguya scent?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that can’t be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.46,0:06:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s more formidable than he appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.75,0:06:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we begin in earnest. The first scent is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.68,0:06:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.76,0:06:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to have made rather a blunder.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And what is the nature of this blunder?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.35,0:06:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I have a store of oleander, which I tried to\Navoid, as it shouldn’t be used in such concoctions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.65,0:06:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m afraid some got mixed in.{}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.20,0:06:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why couldn’t you use this oleander?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.87,0:06:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn’t it a medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.33,0:06:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its leaves are indeed, but a single\Nbreath of the vapor from its branches can kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.50,0:06:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.04,0:06:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.00,0:06:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m afraid I’ve forgotten which of\Nthese five scents contains the oleander.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.60,0:06:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silly me. Silly me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.47,0:06:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must begin again!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.93,0:07:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right! We must start over from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.94,0:07:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.99,0:07:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it is poison, Oosawa will be the first to smell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.04,0:07:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one is neither Princess Kaguya nor the Old Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.72,0:07:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.27,0:07:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.81,0:07:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it not smell at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.69,0:07:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s part of a screen, fragments of a blood-soaked sliding door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.45,0:07:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I prepared it just for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.66,0:08:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For you, Jissonji-san’s killer.{fad}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.55,0:08:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I had intended to tour the house\Nbefore night fell, but I see you beat me to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.93,0:08:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s awfully cold tonight, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.73,0:08:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Throw yourself into the snow if you wish\Nto feel warmer. That’s just common sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.49,0:08:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re Muromachi-han, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.82,0:08:39.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear your prospects for\Npromotion at the palace are dwindling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.20,0:08:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be, Muromachi-han,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.33,0:08:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you’re foolish enough to try and gain\Npower through the Fue-no-Kouji’s Toudaiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.09,0:08:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A desperate move, from a drowning rat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.18,0:08:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Toudaiji is already as good as mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.10,0:09:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody has ever beaten me in a Kumikou.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.52,0:09:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re a fool for trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.65,0:09:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is going on with this room? It stinks of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.48,0:09:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will wait in the next room along.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.82,0:09:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could a smelly swain like\Nyourself know anything of incense?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.37,0:09:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it stinks. It stinks ever so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.10,0:09:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a shameful way to face one’s death.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.46,0:10:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,…chi-ha…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.30,0:10:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muromachi{\alpha&HFF&}-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.63,0:10:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muromachi-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.97,0:10:20.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muromachi{\alpha&HFF&}-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.59,0:10:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muromachi-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.10,0:10:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muroma{\alpha&HFF&}chi-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.44,0:10:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muromachi{\alpha&HFF&}-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.40,0:10:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muromachi-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.45,0:10:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muro{\alpha&HFF&}machi-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.66,0:10:43.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muromachi{\alpha&HFF&}-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.12,0:10:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Muromachi-han.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.84,0:11:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second scent is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.38,0:11:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn’t it, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.51,0:11:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? It smells like burning hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.09,0:11:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Nakarai-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.56,0:11:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you would be able to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.22,0:11:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose hair is it, do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.86,0:12:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1000)}Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.08,0:12:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a lavatory at the end of the hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.13,0:12:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O—O—Oh my. Very kind of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.58,0:12:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you’ll excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.75,0:12:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Ruri, are you in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.02,0:12:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, please just say that the answer is Endless Summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.19,0:12:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the only one who truly desires your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.24,0:12:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The others only want the Toudaiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.15,0:12:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would sell my store and all my worldly possessions for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.45,0:12:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would be penniless, but I would not regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.88,0:12:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it means being with you, I… I…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.70,0:13:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me! Marry me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.86,0:13:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me!{\alpha&HFF&} Me! Me! Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.62,0:13:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me! Me!{\alpha&HFF&} Me! Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.61,0:13:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me! Me! Me!{\alpha&HFF&} Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.62,0:13:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me! Me! Me! Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.52,0:13:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third scent is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.65,0:13:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th—This crazy Kumikou is too much for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.52,0:13:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do not desire the Toudaiji, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.89,0:13:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T—Toudaiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.19,0:14:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was you who suggested this\Nparticular Kumikou, was it not, Oosawa-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.54,0:14:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this scent is the one, the Toudaiji will be mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.37,0:14:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.89,0:14:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, “Ah”?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.18,0:14:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.64,0:14:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that scent contains the oleander.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.44,0:14:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—Wh—Wh—What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.65,0:14:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This scent can’t be the o—o—o—oleander!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.06,0:14:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m so very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.96,0:14:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Antidote! Is there an antidote?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.09,0:14:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to remember that a great quantity of water can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.72,0:15:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.17,0:15:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water!{\alpha&HFF&} Water! Water! Water! Water! Water! Water! Water!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.72,0:15:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water! Water!{\alpha&HFF&} Water! Water! Water! Water! Water! Water!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.14,0:15:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water! Water! Water!{\alpha&HFF&} Water! Water! Water! Water! Water!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.92,0:15:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water! Water! Water! Water!{\alpha&HFF&} Water! Water! Water! Water!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.50,0:15:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water! Water! Water! Water! Water!{\alpha&HFF&} Water! Water! Water!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.01,0:15:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water! Water! Water! Water! Water! Water!{\alpha&HFF&} Water! Water!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.30,0:15:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water! Water! Water! Water! Water! Water! Water!{\alpha&HFF&} Water!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.75,0:15:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Water! Water! Water! Water! Water! Water! Water! Water!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.03,0:15:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An ordinary medicine seller could not\Nafford such a rare medicine as oleander.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.12,0:15:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s what you want to say, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.16,0:15:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.92,0:15:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether or not it was real,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.21,0:15:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as long as he,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.09,0:15:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,no, {\i1}they{\i0}, realized that their lives\Nwere over, it fulfilled its purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.02,0:15:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I only intended to draw you\Nout, then leave you to your own devices,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.02,0:16:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but maintaining the status quo is so terribly dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.52,0:16:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I simply had to meddle a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.83,0:16:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes,{\alpha&HFF&} there was never anyone else in this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.16,0:16:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there was never anyone else in this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.87,0:16:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Other than yourself and those sad souls,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.67,0:16:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,unaware of their own deaths,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.01,0:16:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you once possessed and killed, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.35,0:16:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You watched me prepare\Nincense all by myself in an empty room,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.82,0:16:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and laughed at me from in there, didn’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.98,0:16:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn’t you, Mononoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.11,0:16:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.70,0:17:00.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Mononoke whose form changes\Ndepending on where it is seen. Such is the Nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.49,0:17:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I should call you Toudaiji now, shouldn’t I?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.30,0:17:13.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have determined the Mononoke’s Form.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.69,0:17:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The others told me of your Truth and Regret, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.98,0:17:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You killed those that came in pursuit of the rumored Toudaiji,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.20,0:17:30.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and had them repeat an endless\Nseries of Kumikou, night after night.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.23,0:17:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your Truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.25,0:17:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To the layman’s eye, you are naught but rotten old wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.84,0:17:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to remain yourself, you needed someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.76,0:17:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}anyone{\i0} to say you were more than just another tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.13,0:17:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is your Regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.93,0:18:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, though, this was going a bit far, don’t you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.41,0:18:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.46,0:18:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will become yet another among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.60,0:18:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.89,0:18:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.09,0:18:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So dark! So dark!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.11,0:18:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to me! Come to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.45,0:19:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Form, Truth, Regret, assembled thus,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.07,0:19:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my sword shall be released!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.74,0:19:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Released!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.64,0:19:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—What are you going to do to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.64,0:20:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without a flame to burn it, the\Nwood will never release its true scent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.17,0:20:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a peaceful garden this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.95,0:20:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.61,0:20:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the scent expires.
